<p>GDP growth: 2.8% GDP: $28bn (PPP: $36bn) Inflation: 3.0% Population: 2.2m GDP per head: $12,850 (PPP: $16,360)</p>

<p>Valdis Zatlers, ousted by the legislature as president after engineering its dissolution, lost out to the pro-Russian Harmony Centre in the resulting legislative election in late 2011. But his newly minted party looked likely to take power anyway, at the head of a centre-right majority coalition. Whoever governs, there is little wiggle room over policy. An IMF rescue programme expires as the year begins, but another may be in the works, and preparations to join the euro zone in 2014 (assuming it still exists) will impose overarching policy guidelines.Â </p>

